The paper deals with object detection in wide area motion imagery (WAMI) using computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel two-stage spatio-temporal CNN, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also experiments with different state-of-the-art methods and compares their results, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with video frames and motion imagery, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
